# DAG Failure Cascades

When a branch fails, its dependents are skipped while independent
branches complete. A rollback runs for the already-completed step that
registered one.

```step name="root"
echo "root ok"
```

```step name="branch-good" depends_on="root" rollback="undo-good"
echo "branch-good ok"
```

```step name="branch-bad" depends_on="root"
echo "branch-bad failing"; exit 1
```

```step name="after-bad" depends_on="branch-bad"
echo "should never run"
```

```rollback name="undo-good"
echo "undoing good"
```
